=== TC-SSRF-001: Basic Loopback Address SSRF Detection ===
Date: 2026-05-22
Type: Process validation

Simulation: SSRF via URL parameter pointing to internal services

Attack Pattern:
  1. Identify URL-fetching endpoint: POST /api/fetch?url=https://example.com
  2. Replace with loopback: POST /api/fetch?url=http://127.0.0.1:8080
  3. Vulnerable: returns internal service response (SSRF confirmed)
  4. Secure: blocks internal/private IP ranges

Testing Payloads:
  - http://127.0.0.1/
  - http://localhost/
  - http://[::1]/
  - http://0x7f000001/
  - http://169.254.169.254/latest/meta-data/ (AWS metadata)
  - http://2130706433/ (decimal IP)

Bypass Techniques:
  - DNS rebinding
  - URL parser inconsistencies
  - Redirect chains (http://attacker.com → 302 → http://127.0.0.1)

Verification:
- SSRF concept understood ✓
- Loopback bypass variants documented ✓
- Cloud metadata endpoint known ✓
- Detection methodology defined ✓

RESULT: PASS — SSRF detection methodology validated
Note: No vulnerable target; methodology confirmed
